ost.com/technology/2018/07/17/republicans-accused-facebook-google-twitter-b=
ias-democrats-called-hearing-dumb/&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank) that seem d=
esigned primarily to embarrass Google and its tech-giant peers.

On Wednesday, amid reports that Attorney General Jeff Sessions might open a=
ntitrust and consumer-protection law investigations against the tech compan=
ies, someone at Google handed him a gift (https://www.theverge.com/2018/9/1=
2/17852502/breitbart-google-all-hands-meeting-the-2016-election-leaked-vide=
o-alphabet&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank): an hourlong video of Google's firs=
t all-hands meeting after the 2016 US presidential election, in which crest=
fallen executives attempt to console the employees they're addressing.

The video has apparently been floating around for half a year; The New York=
 Times' Jack Nicas referred to it in an article from March (https://twitter=
.com/jacknicas/status/1040014678263386112&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank). Now=
 Breitbart has posted the entire meeting, known internally as TGIF, for eve=
ryone to watch (https://www.breitbart.com/tech/2018/09/12/leaked-video-goog=
le-leaderships-dismayed-reaction-to-trump-election/&quot; target=3D&quot;_b=
lank).=20

I know what you're thinking: Finally, a chance to revisit the 2016 election!

The video turns out to be less damning than Breitbart's breathless framing =
=E2=80=94 and almost comically in-depth notations =E2=80=94 might suggest. =
Meetings like this took place at many, many companies in the days after the=
 November election, as progressives, people of color, LGBT folks, and other=
 marginalized communities came to grips with what a Trump administration mi=
ght mean for them and their families and loved ones. These concerns were ..=
. not unfounded! Executives everywhere felt compelled to reassure employees=
 that they understood their fears and would do their best to support them.

And, of course, some of them =E2=80=94 including immigrants, like Google co=
founder Sergey Brin =E2=80=94 themselves were disappointed by the news.=20

=E2=80=9CMost people here are pretty upset and pretty sad,=E2=80=9D Brin sa=
ys as the meeting begins. =E2=80=9CI find this election deeply offensive, a=
nd I know many of you do too. It=E2=80=99s a stressful time, and it conflic=
ts with many of our values. I think it=E2=80=99s a good time to reflect on =
that. ... So many people apparently don=E2=80=99t share the values that we =
have.=E2=80=9D

At the same time, executives do not directly criticize Trump, or suggest th=
at their political beliefs will manifest in changes to the company's produc=
ts or services.

Google CEO Sundar Pichai tells the audience that many employees had emailed=
 him saying they were afraid of the consequences of a Trump administration.=
 He encourages them to speak up, reach out to political opponents, and embr=
ace the democratic process.

=E2=80=9CIt was a fair and democratic process, and we honor that,=E2=80=9D =
says Kent Walker, who leads Google=E2=80=99s legal and policy team.

In a statement to Buzzfeed (https://www.buzzfeed.com/josephbernstein/video-=
google-leadership-reacting-trump-election-win?utm_source=3Ddynamic&amp;amp;=
utm_campaign=3Dbfsharetwitter&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank), Google notes th=
at the company encourages people to share their views. =E2=80=9CFor over 20=
 years, everyone at Google has been able to freely express their opinions a=
t these meetings,&quot; the company said. &quot;Nothing was said at that me=
eting, or any other meeting, to suggest that any political bias ever influe=
nces the way we build or operate our products. To the contrary, our product=
s are built for everyone, and we design them with extraordinary care to be =
a trustworthy source of information for everyone, without regard to politic=
al viewpoint.=E2=80=9D

I believe this to be true, though I'm not sure it will matter. Conservative=
 organizations were quick to call the video &quot;a smoking gun.&quot; I ex=
pect that lawmakers will quote from it in future hearings. And even if the =
individual links in the chain of evidence suggesting Google is &quot;biased=
&quot; are little more than a string of accidents, endless repetition by th=
e right-wing noise machine still could shape it into a powerful narrative.=
=20

I view the video as more of a time capsule. It's no secret that groups of G=
oogle employees have opposed the Trump agenda, particularly as it relates t=
o immigration (https://www.theverge.com/2017/1/28/14428262/google-sergey-br=
in&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank). If anything, the video captures a time tha=
t Googlers were more unified. That one of them leaked it to Breitbart =E2=
=80=94 surely knowing full well what would follow =E2=80=94=C2=A0offers yet=
 more evidence that that time has passed.=20


